article.description: Amber Harris scored 16 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Xavier (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) to a 73-47 win over La Salle on Saturday.
article.headline: Harris racks up fourth straight double-double as Musketeers cruise
article.linkText: No. 12 Xavier rolls behind Harris' double-double
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA --  Amber Harris scored 16 points and had 11 rebounds to lead Xavier (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) to a 73-47 win over La Salle on Saturday.

Harris had her fourth straight double-double after missing most of last season with a knee injury. Tyeasha Moss and Ta'Shia Phillips each scored 14 points and Katie Rutan added 11 for Xavier (12-3, 2-0 Atlantic 10).

The Musketeers went on a 36-15 run in the first half to build a 45-22 halftime lead.

Ashley Gale led La Salle (5-13, 0-3) with 10 points and Chelsea Conner added eight.

The Explorers were playing without high scorer Morgan Robertson (11.1 points), who missed the game with a knee injury.
